{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":825,"text":"Have you heard the news?"},{"time":2488,"text":"We're in a clean energy revolution."},{"time":5462,"text":"And where I live in Berkeley, California,"},{"time":7476,"text":"it seems like every day I see a new roof\nwith new solar panels going up,"},{"time":11784,"text":"electric car in the driveway."},{"time":13812,"text":"Germany sometimes gets\nhalf its power from solar,"},{"time":17051,"text":"and India is now committed\nto building 10 times more solar"},{"time":21568,"text":"than we have in California,"},{"time":22920,"text":"by the year 2022."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24896,"text":"Even nuclear seems to be\nmaking a comeback."},{"time":27874,"text":"Bill Gates is in China\nworking with engineers,"},{"time":30943,"text":"there's 40 different companies\nthat are working together"},{"time":33764,"text":"to try to race to build the first\nreactor that runs on waste,"},{"time":37113,"text":"that can't melt down"},{"time":38374,"text":"and is cheaper than coal."},{"time":40492,"text":"And so you might start to ask:"},{"time":43430,"text":"Is this whole global warming problem"},{"time":45251,"text":"going to be a lot easier to solve\nthan anybody imagined?"},{"time":48504,"text":"That was the question we wanted to know,"},{"time":50479,"text":"so my colleagues and I decided\nto take a deep dive into the data."},{"time":53745,"text":"We were a little skeptical of some parts"},{"time":55796,"text":"of the clean energy revolution story,"},{"time":57827,"text":"but what we found really surprised us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60611,"text":"The first thing is that clean\nenergy has been increasing."},{"time":64545,"text":"This is electricity from clean energy\nsources over the last 20 years."},{"time":69023,"text":"But when you look at\nthe percentage of global electricity"},{"time":72765,"text":"from clean energy sources,"},{"time":74128,"text":"it's actually been in decline\nfrom 36 percent to 31 percent."},{"time":78718,"text":"And if you care about climate change,"},{"time":80924,"text":"you've got to go in the opposite direction"},{"time":83094,"text":"to 100 percent of our electricity\nfrom clean energy sources,"},{"time":86668,"text":"as quickly as possible."},{"time":88290,"text":"Now, you might wonder,"},{"time":89471,"text":"\"Come on, how much could five percentage\npoints of global electricity be?\""},{"time":93364,"text":"Well, it turns out to be quite a bit."},{"time":95155,"text":"It's the equivalent of 60 nuclear plants"},{"time":98322,"text":"the size of Diablo Canyon,\nCalifornia's last nuclear plant,"},{"time":101957,"text":"or 900 solar farms the size of Topaz,"},{"time":105650,"text":"which is one of the biggest\nsolar farms in the world,"},{"time":108203,"text":"and certainly our biggest in California."},{"time":111587,"text":"A big part of this is simply\nthat fossil fuels are increasing"},{"time":114855,"text":"faster than clean energy."},{"time":116132,"text":"And that's understandable."},{"time":117395,"text":"There's just a lot of poor countries"},{"time":119134,"text":"that are still using wood\nand dung and charcoal"},{"time":121611,"text":"as their main source of energy,"},{"time":123220,"text":"and they need modern fuels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124695,"text":"But there's something else going on,"},{"time":126668,"text":"which is that one of those clean energy\nsources in particular"},{"time":130747,"text":"has actually been on the decline\nin absolute terms,"},{"time":134179,"text":"not just relatively."},{"time":135704,"text":"And that's nuclear."},{"time":136942,"text":"You can see its generation\nhas declined seven percent"},{"time":140615,"text":"over the last 10 years."},{"time":142476,"text":"Now, solar and wind have been\nmaking huge strides,"},{"time":145108,"text":"so you hear a lot of talk\nabout how it doesn't really matter,"},{"time":148040,"text":"because solar and wind\nis going to make up the difference."},{"time":150802,"text":"But the data says something different."},{"time":152682,"text":"When you combine all the electricity\nfrom solar and wind,"},{"time":155751,"text":"you see it actually barely makes up\nhalf of the decline from nuclear."},{"time":161758,"text":"Let's take a closer look\nin the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164100,"text":"Over the last couple of years --\nreally 2013, 2014 --"},{"time":167915,"text":"we prematurely retired\nfour nuclear power plants."},{"time":171408,"text":"They were almost entirely\nreplaced with fossil fuels,"},{"time":174231,"text":"and so the consequence\nwas that we wiped out"},{"time":177761,"text":"almost as much clean energy\nelectricity that we get from solar."},{"time":182711,"text":"And it's not unique to us."},{"time":186113,"text":"People think of California\nas a clean energy and climate leader,"},{"time":189208,"text":"but when we looked at the data,"},{"time":191240,"text":"what we found is that, in fact,"},{"time":192765,"text":"California reduced emissions more slowly\nthan the national average,"},{"time":195992,"text":"between 2000 and 2015."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198359,"text":"What about Germany?"},{"time":199618,"text":"They're doing a lot of clean energy."},{"time":201675,"text":"But when you look at the data,"},{"time":203430,"text":"German emissions have actually\nbeen going up since 2009,"},{"time":206732,"text":"and there's really not anybody\nwho's going to tell you"},{"time":209331,"text":"that they're going to meet\ntheir climate commitments in 2020."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213137,"text":"The reason isn't hard to understand."},{"time":214913,"text":"Solar and wind provide power\nabout 10 to 20 percent of the time,"},{"time":218240,"text":"which means that when\nthe sun's not shining,"},{"time":220312,"text":"the wind's not blowing,"},{"time":221688,"text":"you still need power for your hospitals,"},{"time":223863,"text":"your homes, your cities, your factories."},{"time":226617,"text":"And while batteries have made\nsome really cool improvements lately,"},{"time":230545,"text":"the truth is, they're just never\ngoing to be as efficient"},{"time":233277,"text":"as the electrical grid."},{"time":234500,"text":"Every time you put electricity\ninto a battery and take it out,"},{"time":237651,"text":"you lose about 20 to 40\npercent of the power."},{"time":241470,"text":"That's why when, in California,"},{"time":244087,"text":"we try to deal with all the solar\nwe've brought online --"},{"time":246825,"text":"we now get about 10 percent\nof electricity from solar --"},{"time":249613,"text":"when the sun goes down,\nand people come home from work"},{"time":252279,"text":"and turn on their air conditioners\nand their TV sets,"},{"time":254793,"text":"and every other appliance in the house,"},{"time":256715,"text":"we need a lot of natural gas backup."},{"time":259200,"text":"So what we've been doing"},{"time":260389,"text":"is stuffing a lot of natural gas\ninto the side of a mountain."},{"time":263616,"text":"And that worked pretty well for a while,"},{"time":265889,"text":"but then late last year,\nit sprung a leak."},{"time":268904,"text":"This is Aliso Canyon."},{"time":270768,"text":"So much methane gas was released,"},{"time":273806,"text":"it was the equivalent of putting\nhalf a million cars on the road."},{"time":277016,"text":"It basically blew through all\nof our climate commitments for the year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281681,"text":"Well, what about India?"},{"time":283029,"text":"Sometimes you have to go places\nto really get the right data,"},{"time":286304,"text":"so we traveled to India a few months ago."},{"time":288309,"text":"We met with all the top officials --\nsolar, nuclear, the rest --"},{"time":291464,"text":"and what they told us is,"},{"time":293029,"text":"\"We're actually having\nmore serious problems"},{"time":295107,"text":"than both Germany and California."},{"time":296806,"text":"We don't have backup;\nwe don't have all the natural gas."},{"time":300363,"text":"And that's just the start of it."},{"time":302919,"text":"Say we want to get\nto 100 gigawatts by 2022."},{"time":305832,"text":"But last year we did just five,"},{"time":307808,"text":"and the year before that, we did five.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":309870,"text":"So, let's just take\na closer look at nuclear."},{"time":312770,"text":"The United Nations Intergovernmental\nPanel on Climate Change"},{"time":316017,"text":"has looked at the carbon content\nof all these different fuels,"},{"time":319012,"text":"and nuclear comes out really low --\nit's actually lower even than solar."},{"time":322969,"text":"And nuclear obviously\nprovides a lot of power --"},{"time":326888,"text":"24 hours a day, seven days a week."},{"time":329465,"text":"During a year, a single plant can provide\npower 92 percent of the time."},{"time":333423,"text":"What's interesting is that\nwhen you look at countries"},{"time":336019,"text":"that have deployed different\nkinds of clean energies,"},{"time":338585,"text":"there's only a few that have done so"},{"time":340509,"text":"at a pace consistent with dealing\nwith the climate crisis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343388,"text":"So nuclear seems like\na pretty good option,"},{"time":345463,"text":"but there's this big problem with it,"},{"time":347525,"text":"which all of you, I'm sure, are aware of,"},{"time":349579,"text":"which is that people really don't like it."},{"time":352431,"text":"There was a study, a survey done\nof people around the world,"},{"time":355646,"text":"not just in the United States or Europe,"},{"time":358173,"text":"about a year and a half ago."},{"time":359728,"text":"And what they found"},{"time":361086,"text":"is that nuclear is actually one\nof the least popular forms of energy."},{"time":364902,"text":"Even oil is more popular than nuclear."},{"time":367356,"text":"And while nuclear kind of\nedges out coal, the thing is,"},{"time":370546,"text":"people don't really fear coal\nin the same way they fear nuclear,"},{"time":374387,"text":"which really operates on our unconscious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376828,"text":"So what is it that we fear?"},{"time":378487,"text":"There's really three things."},{"time":380061,"text":"There's the safety\nof the plants themselves --"},{"time":382325,"text":"the fears that they're going\nto melt down and cause damage;"},{"time":385154,"text":"there's the waste from them;"},{"time":386523,"text":"and there's the association with weapons."},{"time":389562,"text":"And I think, understandably,"},{"time":391022,"text":"engineers look at those concerns\nand look for technological fixes."},{"time":395088,"text":"That's why Bill Gates is in China\ndeveloping advanced reactors."},{"time":398095,"text":"That's why 40 different entrepreneurs\nare working on this problem."},{"time":401243,"text":"And I, myself, have been\nvery excited about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":403498,"text":"We did a report:\n\"How to Make Nuclear Cheap.\""},{"time":405664,"text":"In particular, the thorium reactor\nshows a lot of promise."},{"time":408586,"text":"So when the climate\nscientist, James Hansen,"},{"time":410714,"text":"asked if I wanted to go to China with him"},{"time":413007,"text":"and look at the Chinese\nadvanced nuclear program,"},{"time":415415,"text":"I jumped at the chance."},{"time":416689,"text":"We were there with MIT\nand UC Berkeley engineers."},{"time":419904,"text":"And I had in my mind"},{"time":421604,"text":"that the Chinese would be able\nto do with nuclear"},{"time":423940,"text":"what they did with so many other things --"},{"time":426011,"text":"start to crank out small nuclear\nreactors on assembly lines,"},{"time":429964,"text":"ship them up like iPhones or MacBooks\nand send them around the world."},{"time":434376,"text":"I would get one at home in Berkeley."},{"time":437120,"text":"But what I found was somewhat different."},{"time":439105,"text":"The presentations were all\nvery exciting and very promising;"},{"time":442033,"text":"they have multiple reactors\nthat they're working on."},{"time":444543,"text":"The time came for the thorium reactor,\nand a bunch of us were excited."},{"time":447872,"text":"They went through the whole presentation,\nthey got to the timeline,"},{"time":451295,"text":"and they said,"},{"time":452576,"text":"\"We're going to have\na thorium molten salt reactor"},{"time":456118,"text":"ready for sale to the world"},{"time":458307,"text":"by 2040.\""},{"time":460850,"text":"And I was like, \"What?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":462487,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":463526,"text":"I looked at my colleagues and I was like,"},{"time":465558,"text":"\"Excuse me --"},{"time":467050,"text":"can you guys speed that up a little bit?"},{"time":469404,"text":"Because we're in a little bit\nof a climate crisis right now."},{"time":472502,"text":"And your cities are really\npolluted, by the way.\""},{"time":475252,"text":"And they responded back, they were like,"},{"time":477594,"text":"\"I'm not sure what you've heard\nabout our thorium program,"},{"time":480398,"text":"but we don't have a third of our budget,"},{"time":482337,"text":"and your department of energy\nhasn't been particularly forthcoming"},{"time":485473,"text":"with all that data you guys\nhave on testing reactors.\""},{"time":489382,"text":"And I said, \"Well, I've got an idea."},{"time":491764,"text":"You know how you've got 10 years\nwhere you're demonstrating that reactor?"},{"time":495384,"text":"Let's just skip that part,"},{"time":496980,"text":"and let's just go right\nto commercializing it."},{"time":499354,"text":"That will save money and time.\""},{"time":501379,"text":"And the engineer just\nlooked at me and said,"},{"time":503995,"text":"\"Let me ask you a question:"},{"time":505645,"text":"Would you buy a car that had never\nbeen demonstrated before?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":509913,"text":"So what about the other reactors?"},{"time":511534,"text":"There's a reactor that's coming online\nnow, they're starting to sell it."},{"time":515010,"text":"It's a high-temperature gas reactor."},{"time":516820,"text":"It can't melt down."},{"time":518845,"text":"But it's really big and bulky,\nthat's part of the safety,"},{"time":521604,"text":"and nobody thinks\nit's going to ever get cheaper"},{"time":523916,"text":"than the reactors that we have."},{"time":525880,"text":"The ones that use waste as fuel\nare really cool ideas, but the truth is,"},{"time":529980,"text":"we don't actually know how to do that yet."},{"time":532052,"text":"There's some risk that you'll\nactually make more waste,"},{"time":534671,"text":"and most people think\nthat if you're including"},{"time":537489,"text":"that waste part of the process,"},{"time":539595,"text":"it's just going to make the whole\nmachine a lot more expensive,"},{"time":542586,"text":"it's just adding another complicated step."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545765,"text":"The truth is,"},{"time":547695,"text":"there's real questions about how much\nof that we're going to do."},{"time":550869,"text":"I mean, we went to India and asked\nabout the nuclear program."},{"time":553779,"text":"The government said\nbefore the Paris climate talks"},{"time":556201,"text":"that they were going to do something\nlike 30 new nuclear plants."},{"time":559281,"text":"But when we got there\nand interviewed people"},{"time":561376,"text":"and even looked at the internal documents,"},{"time":563481,"text":"they're now saying\nthey're going to do about five."},{"time":565957,"text":"And in most of the world,\nespecially the rich world,"},{"time":568527,"text":"they're not talking\nabout building new reactors."},{"time":570837,"text":"We're actually talking\nabout taking reactors down"},{"time":573149,"text":"before their lifetimes are over."},{"time":574839,"text":"Germany's actually pressuring\nits neighbors to do that."},{"time":577651,"text":"I mentioned the United States --"},{"time":579482,"text":"we could lose half of our reactors\nover the next 15 years,"},{"time":583849,"text":"which would wipe out 40 percent\nof the emissions reductions"},{"time":586690,"text":"we're supposed to get\nunder the Clean Power Plan."},{"time":589058,"text":"Of course, in Japan, they took\nall their nuclear plants offline,"},{"time":592149,"text":"replaced them with coal,\nnatural gas, oil burning,"},{"time":594526,"text":"and they're only expected to bring\nonline about a third to two-thirds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598112,"text":"So when we went through the numbers,"},{"time":600681,"text":"and just added that up --"},{"time":602028,"text":"how much nuclear do we see\nChina and India bringing online"},{"time":605173,"text":"over the next 15 years,"},{"time":607159,"text":"how much do we see at risk\nof being taken offline --"},{"time":610739,"text":"this was the most startling finding."},{"time":613052,"text":"What we found is that\nthe world is actually at risk"},{"time":616567,"text":"of losing four times more clean energy\nthan we lost over the last 10 years."},{"time":622055,"text":"In other words: we're not\nin a clean energy revolution;"},{"time":625429,"text":"we're in a clean energy crisis."},{"time":628992,"text":"So it's understandable that engineers\nwould look for a technical fix"},{"time":633188,"text":"to the fears that people have of nuclear."},{"time":635166,"text":"But when you consider\nthat these are big challenges to do,"},{"time":637966,"text":"that they're going to take\na long time to solve,"},{"time":640275,"text":"there's this other issue, which is:"},{"time":642045,"text":"Are those technical fixes\nreally going to solve people's fears?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":645828,"text":"Let's take safety."},{"time":647410,"text":"You know, despite what people think,"},{"time":649919,"text":"it's hard to figure out how\nto make nuclear power much safer."},{"time":653076,"text":"I mean, every medical\njournal that looks at it --"},{"time":655418,"text":"this is the most recent study\nfrom the British journal, \"Lancet,\""},{"time":658550,"text":"one of the most respected\njournals in the world --"},{"time":661027,"text":"nuclear is the safest way\nto make reliable power."},{"time":663570,"text":"Everybody's scared of the accidents."},{"time":665375,"text":"So you go look at the accident data --"},{"time":667693,"text":"Fukushima, Chernobyl --"},{"time":669212,"text":"the World Health Organization\nfinds the same thing:"},{"time":671939,"text":"the vast majority of harm\nis caused by people panicking,"},{"time":675938,"text":"and they're panicking\nbecause they're afraid."},{"time":678282,"text":"In other words,"},{"time":679531,"text":"the harm that's caused\nisn't actually caused by the machines"},{"time":683088,"text":"or the radiation."},{"time":684493,"text":"It's caused by our fears."}]},{"cues":[{"time":686573,"text":"And what about the waste?"},{"time":688042,"text":"Everyone worries about the waste."},{"time":689658,"text":"Well, the interesting\nthing about the waste"},{"time":691865,"text":"is how little of it there is."},{"time":693308,"text":"This is just from one plant."},{"time":694709,"text":"If you take all the nuclear waste\nwe've ever made in the United States,"},{"time":698110,"text":"put it on a football field, stacked it up,"},{"time":700333,"text":"it would only reach 20 feet high."},{"time":702580,"text":"And people say it's poisoning\npeople or doing something --"},{"time":705878,"text":"it's not, it's just sitting\nthere, it's just being monitored."},{"time":708801,"text":"There's not very much of it."},{"time":710212,"text":"By contrast, the waste that we don't\ncontrol from energy production --"},{"time":714059,"text":"we call it \"pollution,\" and it kills\nseven million people a year,"},{"time":717207,"text":"and it's threatening very serious\nlevels of global warming."},{"time":720060,"text":"And the truth is that even if we get\ngood at using that waste as fuel,"},{"time":724036,"text":"there's always going to be\nsome fuel left over."},{"time":726335,"text":"That means there's always going to be\npeople that think it's a big problem"},{"time":730230,"text":"for reasons that maybe don't have\nas much to do with the actual waste"},{"time":733558,"text":"as we think."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734851,"text":"Well, what about the weapons?"},{"time":737052,"text":"Maybe the most surprising thing\nis that we can't find any examples"},{"time":740369,"text":"of countries that have nuclear power"},{"time":742346,"text":"and then, \"Oh!\" decide to go get a weapon."},{"time":744798,"text":"In fact, it works the opposite."},{"time":746524,"text":"What we find is the only way we know"},{"time":748714,"text":"how to get rid large numbers\nof nuclear weapons"},{"time":751190,"text":"is by using the plutonium in the warheads"},{"time":754014,"text":"as fuel in our nuclear power plants."},{"time":756490,"text":"And so, if you are wanting to get\nthe world rid of nuclear weapons,"},{"time":760428,"text":"then we're going to need\na lot more nuclear power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763955,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":769515,"text":"As I was leaving China,"},{"time":770905,"text":"the engineer that brought Bill Gates there\nkind of pulled me aside,"},{"time":774118,"text":"and he said, \"You know, Michael,\nI appreciate your interest"},{"time":776923,"text":"in all the different nuclear\nsupply technologies,"},{"time":779654,"text":"but there's this more basic issue,"},{"time":782600,"text":"which is that there's just not\nenough global demand."},{"time":785163,"text":"I mean, we can crank out\nthese machines on assembly lines,"},{"time":788112,"text":"we do know how to make things cheap,"},{"time":789880,"text":"but there's just not enough\npeople that want them.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":792302,"text":"And so, let's do solar and wind\nand efficiency and conservation."},{"time":797268,"text":"Let's accelerate the advanced\nnuclear programs."},{"time":799576,"text":"I think we should triple the amount\nof money we're spending on it."},{"time":803054,"text":"But I just think the most important thing,"},{"time":805467,"text":"if we're going to overcome\nthe climate crisis,"},{"time":807647,"text":"is to keep in mind that the cause\nof the clean energy crisis"},{"time":812922,"text":"isn't from within our machines,"},{"time":815205,"text":"it's from within ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":817557,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":818832,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}